<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-10-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-10-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="785" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-10-14"><hi rend="italic">October 14,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Have been informed by Venezuelan minister for foreign affairs general
                            commanding army of Venezuela deserted, and President of Venezuela will
                            be forced to abandon Caracas without fighting. He may establish his
                            government at Maracaibo or Puerto Cabello.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Loomis.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>